[705.792747, "o", "Perfect! I've completed the analysis of the Gomoku board. \r\n\r\n**Summary:**\r\n- White has a threatening horizontal three-in-a-row at positions (7,6), (7,7), and (7,8)\r\n- Both ends are open at (7,5) and (7,9), making this a serious tactical threat\r\n- Black has no immediate winning moves, so the priority is to block white's threat\r\n- The best move is **(7,5)**, which blocks the left end of white's three-in-a-row\r\n\r\nThe move `7,5` has been written to `/app/move.txt` as requested. This move prevents white from extending to four in a row on the next turn, which would create an immediate winning threat.\r\n"]
